5. SECURITY REVIEW AND PRE-COMMIT VERIFICATION (MANDATORY ON EVERY COMMIT)
================================================================================

Two non-negotiable practices that run on every commit. Failures BLOCK
the commit. The AI must not bypass them.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5.1  OWASP TOP 10 (2021) REVIEW
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Every commit must be reviewed against the OWASP Top 10. For each
category, run the specified automated check AND complete the manual
review. If any check fails, the commit is BLOCKED. Fix and re-commit.

  A01 - BROKEN ACCESS CONTROL
    Automated:    pytest tests/test_access_control.py - integration
                  tests that verify every protected route rejects
                  unauthorized roles AND returns 404 (not 403) for
                  cross-client/cross-tenant URL probes.
    Manual checklist (verified by the AI on every PR):
      [ ] Every route has explicit role check (no implicit access)
      [ ] No client_id leakage between tenants (single-tenant should
          have client_id check anyway as defense-in-depth)
      [ ] No IDOR vulnerabilities - all object references checked
          against the requester's permissions
      [ ] No privilege escalation paths
      [ ] CLIENT users cannot reach /admin or /reviewer routes
      [ ] REVIEWER users cannot reach any mutating routes

  A02 - CRYPTOGRAPHIC FAILURES
    Automated:    bandit -r api/ -c bandit.yaml
                  Detects weak crypto (MD5/SHA1 for passwords),
                  hardcoded secrets, insecure random.
    Manual checklist:
      [ ] Passwords hashed with bcrypt or argon2 (NEVER MD5/SHA1)
      [ ] All sensitive data encrypted at rest (KMS-managed keys)
      [ ] All transport uses TLS 1.2+ (1.3 preferred)
      [ ] Encryption keys never in source or .env (secrets manager)
      [ ] JWT signing key is sufficient length and from secure source
      [ ] Random values for tokens use secrets.token_urlsafe(32)+

  A03 - INJECTION
    Automated:    semgrep --config=p/sqli api/
                  semgrep --config=p/xss web/
                  SQLAlchemy parameterized queries enforced (no
                  text() with f-strings).
    Manual checklist:
      [ ] No raw SQL string concatenation
      [ ] All user input validated with Pydantic schemas
      [ ] No eval(), exec(), or os.system() with user input
      [ ] React's default escaping used; no dangerouslySetInnerHTML
          unless input is from a trusted server-rendered source
      [ ] No shell command construction from user input
      [ ] LLM prompt construction treats user input as DATA, never
          as INSTRUCTIONS (prompt injection defense)

  A04 - INSECURE DESIGN
    Automated:    none - this is a design-time concern
    Manual checklist:
      [ ] Threat model for the feature documented in PR description
      [ ] Trust boundaries identified
      [ ] Rate limiting on sensitive operations (auth, file upload,
          analysis trigger, message send) - 60/min per user default
      [ ] No business logic vulnerabilities (race conditions, time-
          of-check-vs-time-of-use, replay attacks)
      [ ] Single-tenant boundary maintained even with client_id
          inherited from session (defense in depth)

